-- Aboitiz, Manila Electric, Vista Land: Philippine Stock Preview
-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 2012-06-18T00:40:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-18/aboitiz-manila-electric-vista-land-philippine-stock-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Philippine Stock Exchange Index (PCOMP)  fell 1.8 percent to
4,930.63.  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  ,  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  :
Electricity prices may rise in August, Energy Secretary Jose Rene Almendras said in a briefing. Power plants fueled by Royal
Dutch Shell Plc’s Malampaya gas will have to use more expensive
liquid condensates as the gas facility will be shut, Almendras
said. Aboitiz fell 2.3 percent to 31.80 pesos. Manila Electric
lost 0.8 percent to 238 pesos.  Vista Land & Lifescapes Inc. (VLL)  : The builder’s
dividend may rise to 12 centavos this year, Chief Financial
Officer Ricardo Tan said by phone. The company last year paid a
regular and special dividend totaling 10.5 centavos. The stock
fell 2 percent to 3.97 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
